,Recommended,299500,30181754,Posted: 25 February,all,Endominius,"It's not quite a simulation but it's lots of fun. Having said that I'm getting breaks just above the 50 mark which is exactly how I fare in the real game. I like the career mode with the easy early rounds and then tough opponents later on. The AI is OK. Let's face it the computer could play a perfect game every time so it has to be dumbed down, mostly you don't notice. Sometimes it reminds me of early games with my Dad, when he would throw a few shots so I could get some table time. Cue ball action is a little unpredictable but you can mostly get the position you were aiming for.There are significant problems with the Miss Rule (almost like real life). Your AI opponent will never put you back in, no matter how poor their position is. Also the AI will happily throw away a frame, or even a match, with three misses in a row.I like the crowd noises. The oohs and ahhs, the coughing and the occasional ""Go on my Son"" add to the atmosphere. It's a shame they didn't record more variations with Michaela Tabb, she has a gorgeous Scottish accent but sometimes sounds like a robot or answering machine because of overused words.I've had a great time with this game and it cost me less than a pound in a bundle."
