,Recommended,299500,29211484,Posted: 12 January,all,NickyJ,"The score is 58-42, and Spyro Polymiadis is on a 15 score break. Three balls remain: The blue, the pink, and the devious black ball. As Spyro settles in to make the easiest pocket of his life, NickyJ utters the last rites over his own grave before Spyro buries him and all his dreams of a comeback.NickyJ: ""Just make this last blow a painless one.""*Spyro takes his shot and whiffs on it. The blue ball sails wide left of the middle pocket*Spyro: ""DAMNIT""*NickyJ proceeds to sink both the blue and pink balls, setting the score at 58-53. Only the black ball remains to finish this miracle, a simple knock in 5 inches from a corner pocket*NickyJ: ""Goodnight moon. Goodnight stars. Goodnight Spyro Polymiadis.""*Thud-Thud-Thud-Thud-Thud goes the black ball as it bounces off both edges of the corner pocket repeatedly while never entering the pocket*Spyro: ""Haha, tough break Nicky. Tough break. It's time for me to end this.""*THUNK - The black ball bounces off the corner of the rim AGAIN and rolls across the entire table to the opposite side*Somewhere in the chorus of laughs and cries that reverberate through the tournament center, Spyro and NickyJ both curse the name of that stupid Belgian who convinced them to play this irritating game that has ripped their hearts out and stomped on every single dream they ever contrived.-----------------For the $2 I spent on this game during a sale, I won't say it's bad. I certainly wouldn't pay its current full price of $13, though. Having only ever played pool before, snooker was an interesting change. After learning the basics of snooker quite easily from the game, I'll borrow the sage words from the cover of an Othello box to describe it: A minute to learn, a lifetime to master.Pros:+Easy to learn game with simple rules+Simple, easy to understand interface+Varying levels of opponent skill. Sometimes the round is really easy, sometimes really hard. A healthy dose of both throughout each tournament to keep it interesting.+Other billiards type games when snooker gets to be a bit boringCons:-Multiplayer is absolutely broken. Tried to connect 15 times, succeeded 3 times. If you want to buy this game for the multiplayer experience, don't. Period.-The graphics aren't the greatest. Which is fine, you shouldn't be buying a snooker game to look for high definition graphics. Even so, sometimes you just can't avoid noticing people like this:http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/477768284585810206/64BB18D8ECA4F9FFDEDF99EB8BF042EBF90CF5DF/-When I mentioned a ""healthy dose"" of varying skill levels in tournaments, I half lied. Half the opponents are Jekyll Hyde behind a cue stick. Makes an awesome bounce off the wall that would make pros cry in one break; inexplicably sinks the wrong ball for absolutely NO REASON WHATSOEVER the next break.-Mind-numbing physics - I cannot count the number of times I've aimed for the corner pocket and had my ball repeatedly bounce off the corner, going neither into the pocket nor back out onto the table. Once is amusing. Thrice is bemusing. 13th time is agonizing.-Adding onto the above, the ball will never, EVER fly off the table from being hit too hard. If I could climb up onto the table and hit the ball with a golf club, it would never leave the surface of the table. Not really important, but just a petty annoyance of mine.Closing statement: It's not a bad game. If it's under $10, it's worth the money. It's not polished, it's not pretty, but it's still entertaining. Just don't buy it for multiplayer."
