76561198238160278,Recommended,299500,22186930,"Posted: 1 April, 2016",all,mark.greensmith,"If you enjoy a game of snooker now and again, you will enjoy this.  It's not difficult to make high breaks due to the target lines, and you can still manipulate the white exactly as you would in real life.  If you can think a shot, you can play it.  But the AI is merciless, and can also knock up a 30-50 break if you leave the table open.  This is frustrating to watch the AI pot virtually everything it goes for...but it leaves you with a massive stress and tension to try and rack up some big scores each visit (and this IS possible like I said), this tension is what you expect the pro's to feel playing against each other, so I guess this is very accurate.The REAL frustrating thing I find is the lack of fouls the AI gives away.  Most games, you would run out of position and have to cut a ball in very thin with power, so the white would ricochet around and you are praying you wouldn't foul....Inevitably you would occasionally with a bit of bad luck.  But the AI doesn't suffer from this ""bad luck"".  In about 30 frames I gave away about 30 fouls, and the AI gave away 2!!!I would definately recommend this to snooker/pool players, that think about their shots rather than just line it up and hit it...if that's the way you play, the masterful AI will beat you."
